1 Bioinformatics

The BRIC Bioinformatics Core Facility supports researchers at the BRIC center, the University of Copenhagen (UCPH).

The Facility is composed of a multidisciplinary team updated on the latest technologies in molecular biology .

Multiple services are offered:
1. Support in analyzing biological data,
2. Access to a maintained high-performance computational server and,
3. Training in bioinformatics.

  • Data analysis is offered to other scientists at the University of Copenhagen and external institutions, although with a priority to BRIC scientists.

2 Our Services

Our support involves consultation, data analysis, guidance, short & long-term projects and training.

2.1 Consultation

You are always welcome to talk to us! We can work together to understand your needs.

No fee is applied to understand your needs

2.2 Experimental Desing

Including a bioinformatician in an early stage of your project can save you time, work, and money.

2.3 Data Analysis

We adapt to your needs. We can discuss and find together the best way to analyze your data and to provide support for your bioinformatic analysis with your own code or with existing pipelines.

2.4 Standard bioinformatics project

A plus in using our services: We work with optimized pipelines ensuring reproducibility and providing reports.

Estimating hours is always challenging; We estimate a workload of 20 to 30 hrs for a standard analysis of simple datasets of the following types:

  1. Gene Expression
    1.1 RNA-seq
    1.2 ChIP-seq

  2. ATAC-seq

  3. Single Cell

An Example of a Standard RNA-seq dataset analysis

. Initial meeting / communications

. Reading about the project

. Transfer raw sequencing data

. Quality assessment of the data

. Communication with the user

. Alignment of sequencing reads onto the genome of interest and gene quantification

. Differential gene expression analysis

. Functional enrichment

. Report and Data visualization

. Meetings to discuss results and possible follow-ups

2.5 End-To-End

We aim to be able to provide an End-to-End analysis for your project. At the Bioinformatics core facility we take care of your data and data analyses. And we work in close collaboration with other BRIC core facilities to offer and End-To-End analysis
Library Preparation - Sequencing - Bioinformatics

Please, Talk to us for more information on how to get the best of us.

2.6 More services

  • You can also request our services for Data Management. We can prepare and submit your data to any public database.

  • Don’t hesitate to contact us to help you preparing your manuscript!

2.7 Prices

BRIC users: 400 DKK/hour

Other KU users: 500 DKK/hour

External users: 980 DKK/hour

3 About us

Leonor Rib, PhD
leonor.rib@bric.ku.dk

I’m a Computer Scientist with a passion for biology. I hold a PhD in computational biology after doing a PhD in Integrated experimental and computational biology in Switzerland. I have extensive experience in the experimental design and analysis of multiomics and genetic data for more than 15 years in collaboration with hospitals, academic research groups and biotech companies. More details can be found in my LinkedIn profile

I’m originally from Spain, in Catalonia. And if you offer me a “Calçotada” in good company and a good wine with “Porró” you will win my heart! :)

Juliana Assis, PhD

juliana.geraldo@bric.ku.dk

I’m a Biologist with a Ph.D. in Bioinformatics. My field lies broadly in multi-omics data such as Genomic, Transcriptomic, Metagenomic, Metabolomics, and Data Integration. I have extensive experience developing the strategy/experimental design and scientific skills for NGS analysis and long-reads. Making Reproducibility in research is my main focus of study.

You can find more about my work here Google Scholar, and, here: GitHub

My home country is Brazil, and I’m very proud of my cooking skills and my Caipirinha!

Linbu Liao, Ph.D.

linbu.liao@bric.ku.dk

I hold a Ph.D. in Bioinformatics and am a Bioinformatician. As a member of the CellX project, I am tasked with developing Spatial Transcriptomics tools to better comprehend how cells communicate with one another. My relevant work is SC2Spa, a deep learning-based tool to map transcriptome to spatial origins at cellular resolution.

I’m Chinese. In China, I received a bachelor’s degree in petroleum engineering as well as a master’s degree in software engineering. I made substantial adjustments in both disciplines and locations. Staying on the righteous path is more important to me than being who I am supposed to be.
